<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 830
                    The Representative in Bulgaria (
                        Barnes
                    ) to the Acting Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv02</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d830</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">830</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-07-31T09:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-07-31T09:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-31T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-31T09:00:00-05:00" n="830" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d830">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">874.00/7–3145: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 830<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BMB1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barnes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-31T16:00:00+02:00">July 31, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>401. The <gloss target="#t_FF1">FF</gloss> (Fatherland Front) pack is now in full
                    cry after <persName corresp="#p_PND1">Petkov</persName>.</p>
                <p>My next following telegram No. 402<note n="1" xml:id="d830fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> reports portions of radio speech by <persName corresp="#p_DT1">Tsola Dragoicheva</persName> and text of an editorial in
                    this morning[’]s <gloss target="#t_FF1">FF</gloss> newspaper. The fact that
                        <persName corresp="#p_PND1">Petkov</persName>’s letter was a request of [<hi rend="italic">to?</hi>] the Prime Minister that he, the Prime Minister,
                    assure freedom of elections by arranging for Tripartite Allied control has of
                    course not been revealed by <persName corresp="#p_PND1">Petkov</persName>’s
                    pursuers and he (<persName corresp="#p_PND1">Petkov</persName>) has no effective
                        <pb facs="0928" n="734" xml:id="pg_734"/> means of bringing the nature of
                    the document in question to attention of Bulgarian people. It is just this
                    situation that senior Regent <persName corresp="#p_GVY1">Ganev</persName> had in
                    mind when he suggested several days ago that the “Voice of America” in Bulgaria
                    reveal the substance of <persName corresp="#p_PND1">Petkov</persName>’s letter
                    to the Bulgarian people (my telegram 395, July 28<note n="2" xml:id="d830fn2">Not printed.</note> [)]. No objective observer here can doubt that lives of
                        <persName corresp="#p_PND1">Petkov</persName> and his leading supporters are
                    in danger. Every friend of democracy in Bulgaria is looking to Potsdam for some
                    sign of hope.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BMB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Barnes</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
